HEADWORD: Urechitin
<hw>U`re*chi"tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A glucoside extracted from the leaves of a certain plant
(<spn>Urechitis suberecta</spn>) as a bitter white crystalline
substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

